              <div class="content__page-desc">
                
                <h3>General Electric (GE)</h3>
                <p>Repair costs for General Electric (GE) ranges can vary widely depending on the specific issue and model. Generally, GE appliances are known for their reliability and ease of repair. Common repairs, such as replacing a heating element or oven igniter, typically range from <b>$100 to $300</b>, including labor. More complex repairs, such as control board replacement, can cost between <b>$200 and $400</b>. The availability of parts for GE ranges is generally good, which can help keep costs down. However, high-end models or specialized parts may be more expensive to repair.</p>

                <h3>Whirlpool</h3>
                <p>Whirlpool ranges are another popular choice and are generally considered to be affordable when it comes to repairs. Basic repairs, such as replacing control knobs or burner drip pans, usually range from <b>$50 to $150</b>. More involved repairs like fixing a thermostat or control board can cost between <b>$150 and $350</b>. Whirlpool parts are widely available and reasonably priced, which helps keep repair costs manageable. However, the final cost can vary depending on the complexity of the repair and the specific model of the range.</p>

                <h3>Samsung</h3>
                <p>Samsung ranges are known for their advanced features and sleek design, but this can sometimes translate into higher repair costs. Basic repairs, such as replacing an oven light bulb or burner cap, typically cost between <b>$75 and $200</b>. More complex repairs, like fixing a control board or temperature sensor, can range from <b>$200 to $500</b>. Samsung parts may be less readily available than those for some other brands, which can increase both the cost and the time required for repairs. Additionally, the high-tech nature of Samsung ranges may require specialized expertise, which can further drive up repair costs.</p>

                <h3>LG</h3>
                <p>LG ranges are known for their innovative features and high performance, but repair costs can be on the higher side. Simple repairs, such as replacing a heating element or burner cap, generally cost between <b>$80 and $200</b>. More extensive repairs, like replacing a control board or oven door gasket, can range from <b>$200 to $450</b>. The availability of parts for LG ranges is generally good, but specialized or high-end parts can be more expensive. Additionally, the advanced features of LG ranges may require specialized knowledge for repairs, potentially increasing labor costs.</p>

                <h3>Frigidaire</h3>
                <p>Frigidaire ranges are often praised for their durability and cost-effectiveness, making them relatively affordable to repair. Basic repairs, such as replacing oven racks or burner drip pans, typically cost between <b>$50 and $150</b>. More significant repairs, like fixing a bake element or thermostat, usually range from <b>$150 to $300</b>. Frigidaire parts are widely available and reasonably priced, which helps keep repair costs low. However, high-end models or specialized parts may still incur higher costs.</p>

                <h3>Bosch</h3>
